</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-33_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>Support workers, also known as healthcare assistants or care assistants, provide practical and emotional support to individuals who require assistance with daily living activities due to illness, disability, or age-related conditions. Their duties may include personal care, medication administration, meal preparation, and companionship.





 

  
<br>
